headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 39 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists, and the playoff-bound Dallas Mavericks continued their late-season surge, beating the Charlotte Hornets 130-104 on Tuesday night for their 15th win in 17 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 39 in triple-double as Mavs beat Hornets 130-104, clinch playoff spot

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 37 points and 11 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers extended their winning streak to six games with a 120-102 win over the Detroit Pistons on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 37 as 76ers beat Pistons 120-102 for 6th straight victory

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 30 points, Pascal Siakam added 16 points in 26 minutes in his second game back in Toronto and the Indiana Pacers pulled away early in the second half and beat the Raptors 140-123 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton, Siakam power the Pacers to a 140-123 win over the Raptors

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored four of his 33 points in the second overtime and the Miami Heat outlasted the Atlanta Hawks 117-111 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 33, Butler adds 25 as the Heat outlast the Hawks 117-111 in 2 OTs

headlines.description: — On the night they finally snapped their four-game skid, the Milwaukee Bucks encountered an entirely different reason for worry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks withstand Antetokounmpo's injury to beat Celtics 104-91. Teams combined for record-low 2 FTs

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: - Jalen Brunson scored 45 in his second straight 40-point game, and the New York Knicks beat the Chicago Bulls 128-117 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 45 in second straight 40-point game, Knicks beat Bulls 128-117

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored a season-high 37 points and the Houston Rockets snapped a five-game skid with a 118-106 victory over the Orlando Magic on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet has season-high 37 as Rockets get 118-106 win over Magic, who fall into tie for fourth

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 18 points, seven blocks, seven rebounds and six assists, Julian Champagnie added 17 points, and the San Antonio Spurs rode a third-quarter outburst to a 102-87 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama has 18 points, seven blocks as Spurs ease past Grizzlies 102-87

headlines.description: — ​Anthony Edwards scored a career-high 51 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves overcame an early 21-point deficit with a dominant second half to beat the Washington Wizards 130-121 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores career-high 51 points, Timberwolves rally to beat Wizards 130-121

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 40 points in his return from injury, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied from a 20-point deficit to defeat Sacramento 112-105 on Tuesday night as the Kings' Domantas Sabonis had his double-double streak halted at 61...
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 40 as Thunder top Kings; Sabonis' double-double streak ends at 61 games

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 28 points, Nikola Jokic tallied 28 points and 13 rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets pushed past the shorthanded Utah Jazz 111-95 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray and Jokic score 28 each as the Nuggets run past shorthanded Jazz 111-95

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 27 points, Stephen Curry had 23 and the Golden State Warriors capitalized on Anthony Davis' injury absence for a 134-120 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors make 26 3-pointers, roar past Lakers for a key 134-120 win in Anthony Davis' injury absence

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had 16 points, 15 rebounds and 15 assists for his first triple-double of the season and 199th of his career, and the Los Angeles Clippers built a 31-point lead in the first quarter before holding on late for a 105-92 victory over...
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers build 31-point lead in first quarter and hold on late to beat Suns 105-92

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III had 31 points and eight rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Portland Trail Blazers 110-100 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy, McCollum help Pelicans beat Trail Blazers 110-100
